If the optic nerve (II) or olfactory tract is interrupted, will it regenerate? <image 1> 

A. No, will not regenerate.
B. Yes, will regenerate.

A. No, will not regenerate.

The optic nerve (II) and olfactory tract are part of the peripheral nervous system and do not have the ability to regenerate once damaged.
